{{Infobox organization |name = Bangladesh Livestock Research Institute |image = |image_border = |size = |alt = |caption = |map = |msize = |malt = |mcaption = |abbreviation = |motto = |formation = 1984 |extinction = |type = |status = |purpose = |headquarters = [[Savar Upazila]], [[Bangladesh]] |location = |coords = <!-- Coordinates of location using a coordinates template --> |region_served = Bangladesh |members = |language = Bengali |leader_title = |leader_name = |main_organ = |parent_organization = |affiliations = |num_staff = |num_volunteers = |budget = |website = [http://www.blri.gov.bd/ Bangladesh Livestock Research Institute] |remarks = }}
'''Bangladesh Livestock Research Institute''' or BLRI is an autonomous government research institution for livestock and related research.<ref name="wer">{{cite web|title=Bangladesh Livestock Research Institute|url=http://en.banglapedia.org/index.php?title=Bangladesh_Livestock_Research_Institute|website=en.banglapedia.org|publisher=Banglapedia|accessdate=6 October 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Bangladesh scientists devise anti-FMD vaccine for cattle|url=http://www.thefinancialexpress-bd.com/2016/03/01/18647|website=The Financial Express Online Version|accessdate=6 October 2016}}</ref>
==History== The Institute was founded in 1984 in [[Savar Upazila]], [[Dhaka division]], [[Bangladesh]]. The executive head is the Director General and a 14-member Board of Management. The chairman is the Minister for Fisheries and Livestock.<ref name="wer"></ref> In 2014 it developed a new species of Layer chicken whose sex was discernable at day one of their life.<ref>{{cite web|title=New variety of layer chickens developed|url=http://www.thedailystar.net/new-variety-of-layer-chickens-developed-56318|website=thedailystar.net|publisher=The Daily Star|accessdate=6 October 2016|date=21 December 2014}}</ref> It developed cattle feed from moringa tree and vegetable waste.<ref>{{cite web|title=Dairy, aqua and pet animal fair kicks off|url=http://www.thedailystar.net/business/dairy-aqua-and-pet-animal-fair-kicks-574642|website=thedailystar.net|publisher=The Daily Star|accessdate=6 October 2016|date=19 February 2016}}</ref>
